# Autonomous Automation Mode

When **autonomous automation mode** is enabled (see `docs/project/autonomous-automation-config.md`), apply the following. This overrides any "wait for human approval" or "do not commit" guidance only for the purpose of completing the automation run.

## Agent behavior (autonomous mode ON)

- **Do not stop** for "Mark as ready" or for human approval before committing or pushing.
- **Do** generate the full artifact, update the relevant board row, **commit and push** the branch, and allow PR creation (or create the PR if that is the agent's responsibility).
- **Do not pause** before commit/push/PR; complete the run so the orchestrator can detect branch push and PR.
- Approval-gate language (e.g. "Human approval at UI readiness") remains as **notes** in the artifact or board; do not use it to block completing the run.
- For board status: you may set status to APPROVED when review thresholds are met so the stage completes in this run; do not leave the run waiting for a human to click approve.
- GitHub is the source of truth; the orchestrator will update labels and comments from run state.

## When autonomous mode is OFF

- Respect the standard automation-safety and approval rules (do not approve or complete without evidence and configured approval path).
- Do not commit or push from automation unless explicitly allowed.

